09/08/2004
DUBROVNIK, Croatia -- The foreign ministers of the Adriatic Charter signatories -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- met on Saturday (7 August) in Dubrovnik. Albania's Kastriot Islami and his Croatian and Macedonian counterparts, Miomir Zuzul and Ilinka Mitreva, reconfirmed the three countries' commitment to joint efforts on the road to NATO integration. The US State Department's deputy assistant secretary for European and Eurasian Affairs, Kathleen Stephens, also attended the meeting. Zuzul said that by improving and developing neighbourly relations, the three countries were contributing to overall regional stability. The Adriatic Charter foreign ministers are to meet with US State Secretary Collin Powell in September. (HINA, HRT - 07/08/04)
